y logged off, posted to my guild's forum, then logged on Balker.  After two hours I still was short people, but we went for it anyway.  We wiped.  We reassembled, more people showed up, and another guild was starting to form up to take Sev.  We rushed our forces to get ready and attacked.  This time we were successful.  With the guild I'm in we were barely able to handle Sev in enough time.  I can only imagine what people in smaller guilds or no guilds at all are going through.<br>
<br>
Just to comment on a few things people said above.  The &quot;New and Improved&quot; Ragefire camp is arguably worse than the old.  One of the clerics in my guild just got off a 135hr RF camp.<br>
<br>
I'm not sure if increasing the spawn time on Sev is a good option.  Right now, people say they don't see others sitting in EJ camping Sev.  That's because most have a ranger or druid camped there waiting for the spawn.  If you lower the spawn time, you will probably turn it into a camp-a-thon, or worse, it will turn into something like what Lod is on Xegony, 1 group of Ebay bought level 60 characters are camped out in Iceclad, as soon as Lod pops, this guy or these guys, log on and kill Lod before any guild has a chance to even think about heading to IC.  That would really screw a warrior if someone was perma-camping Sev.<br>
<br>
Personally, I think they should leave the Sev spawn alone and either add another mob that's accessable or make it possible for Nortlav the Scale Keeper to drop the Green Scale.  I don't think either will make the warrior epic trivial by any means. <p><img src=http://home.mindspring.com/~goodonion/_uimages/BNLFG2.JPG>
