Val'Kori</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uriggens.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Riggens</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/5/02 1:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=307.topic&index=58>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I gave in finally</span><hr size=1> I was like alot of the warriors here and thought the green dragon scale was a serious bottleneck for the epic. Untill I started to camp him. I parked a 41 druid close to the staircase and would play my warrior on my main machine while tracking SEV on my POS second machine. Here is the info I gathered from 2 weeks of tracking SEV:<br>
<br>
1) Have your guild on call, so to speak. Post on your boards that you are camping this mob and need forces within a moments notice to gather to EJ and prep for SEV. SEV is a GUILD DEPENDANT MOB. You need your guilds support to drop everything and come to EJ on your call. Establish this first and foremost. <br>
2) SEV is a 3 day spawn. It's not exact, but I watched him spawn 4 times in 12 days, with no patches in between. I would say give or take 2 hours inbetween last death and new pop. After patches, Im not sure the spawn time. I would just try to watch zone as much as you can after patch or find out when he was killed and come back 3 days later. If another guild kills him, start the timer, you have a advantage now, use it. <br>
3) EJ is very easy to get to and fast, you can port right in and run to the staircase in 2-3 minutes, depending on your zone times.<br>
4) When SEV does spawn, scan the zone for people. If no guild has started gathering (meaning you don't see more then 6 people of any guild here yet) call out in guild chat to get to EJ ASAP. <br>
5) Its now just a rat race to get the forces there first. Win the race, win the spawn. <br>
6) Once you have people there, try to get everyone to 160+ PR 160 + MR. On pull have guildmates remove haste from SEV ASAP, cancel magic. Then have shammy Malo and Slow him. MA engage, go defensive, build agro, call in troops, nuke at 55, dead dragon. <br>
7) If he doesn't drop scale, go smoke and calm down, write down time he died, and come back in 3 days, and track him again. <br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   If you are persistant and put in the time, you'll get the scale. <br>
<br>
Just my 2 cents of advice on what worked for me. I agree, its a bottleneck and the alt option Hoskgar (sp) sucks balls. Your best bet is SEV, just get your guild ready to drop EVERYTHING and get to EJ ASAP and youll get the mob eventually. <br>
<br>
And reguardless of what people say about replacing it, it's still a great weapon and it holds agro very well. What other weapon has the ability of being able to be used has a 2 hander or two 1 handers? The 2 hander version procs so much for me (I double proc it alot) I can hold agro with a 2 hander over some duel wielders =) The epic gives a huge DEX increase as noted in this thread, and helps it proc alot. It has about 190 HP on it, with the 15 stm included. 12 AC on the blue one to make up for lesser weapons that had AC on them you were probably using before. 10 to all resists. It's not a super fast weapon in the 1 hander mode like Zek but with haste item and chanter haste, your doing some nice damage, and you hit harder then with Zek by far. Try out your mightystrike now =) It's look, (IMO), is unmatched by any other epic by far. <br>
<br>
Good Luck to all warriors questing this gem...When you get it, you'll have a perma smile for weeks =) <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=124692" target="_new"><B><FONT COLOR="#1E90FF">Riggens Warchild </FONT></B></a>
